author: Mahteindono degozaru!
text:
“Sorry” works when a mistake is made but not when trust is broken. So in life, make mistakes but never break trust. Forgiving is easy, but forgetting and trusting again is sometimes impossible.
— Anonymous

author: Mahteindono degozaru!
text:
And now imagine being at their shoes, with all that has happened and one day all you get back is a simple word “sorry”

Does their response makes sense?

author: Mahteindono degozaru!
text: When you broke that trust, you break every part of them that they laid for you. Parts that no one in this world has ever seen or received from them. The love, dedication and everything they stand for, dies along with that trust.

author: Mahteindono degozaru!
text:
That sorry isn’t giving back them what they lost.
That sorry will not heal any wound they have.
That sorry compromised their ability to ever trust anyone again.
That sorry can never change how they see the world after.
That sorry will not make them the person they once were.

author: Mahteindono degozaru!
text:
Submissiveness is an act of trust and with it they believed you’ll always stand by them. At that most tender state you inhumanly break their trust and emotions before walking away, leaving then helpless and in despair.

And you wonder why “sorry” isn’t enough?
